   <head>ABSOLUTION.</head>
  </front>
  <body>
   <lg xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" type="poem">
    <lg n="1" stanza_type="sestet">
     <l n="1" met="--+|--+|--+|--+" line_length="12">IT blew an hard storm, and in utmost confusion</l>
     <l n="2" met="--+|--+|--+|--+" line_length="12">The sailors all hurried to get absolution;</l>
     <l n="3" met="--+|--+|--+|--+" line_length="12">Which done, and the weight of the sins they'd confess'd,</l>
     <l n="4" met="--+|--+|--+|--+" line_length="12">Was transfer'd, as they thought, from themselves to the priest</l>
     <l n="5" met="--+|--+|--+|--+" line_length="12">To lighten the ship, and conclude their devotion,</l>
     <l n="6" met="--+|--+|--+|--+" line_length="12">They toss'd the poor parson souse into the ocean.</l>
    </lg>
   </lg>
